==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cresol
<hw>Cre"sol</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"s⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Creosote</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of three
metameric substances, <chform>CH3.C6H4.OH</chform>, homologous with and
resembling phenol. They are obtained from coal tar and wood tar, and are
colorless, oily liquids or solids. <note>[Called also <altname>cresylic
acid</altname>.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cresorcin</ent>⟦br⟧
